50|$|<b>Capital</b> <b>Leasing</b> is {{a subset}} of the leasing {{industry}} and allows companies to get the use of the equipment without having to tie up their capital. Unlike traditional loans where the business is given funds to purchase the asset, <b>capital</b> <b>leases</b> rely on the lessor owning the leased item as collateral during the life of the lease, as well as other covenants. In addition to providing greater legal control over the item, the lessor can also reduce their tax liability through depreciation.|$|R
