40|$|This study uses price {{appreciation}} and bargaining power measures to deter-mine whether current accounting standards are effective at classifying leases by ownership risk. I use a regression model, {{and find that}} there is a positive and significant relationship between changes in <b>capital</b> <b>leases</b> and my prox-ies for price {{appreciation and}} the interaction between price appreciation and bargaining power. I also find, however, that it’s possible that operating leases may be increasing faster, which would discount the theory that these standards are operating properly. These results should be cause for further study on the subject and should be interesting to regulators...|$|R
